at its purpose is to &#x0093;summon the souls&#x0094; of readers who have lost themselves in the turbulence of a society in the transition to modernity&#x2014;and then to restore these lost souls to the bodies they have left. An evocation of both flesh and spirit, these Jiangnan stories give voice to the complex and disturbing experience of women in a changing society.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aKing, Richard.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Hawaii Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000z978311056415040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082486434740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780824864347423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780824864347.jpg  a978-3-11-056415-0  University of Hawaii Press Archive eBook-Package Pre-2000b2000  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK